subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. 
Female
. Frons distinctly pilose, sculpture not visible due to pilosity; clypeus incised apico-medially, forming two lobes, yellowish brown macula on upper clypeal margin (
Fig. 2
); pronotal collar dorsally with yellowish brown band, medially notched; mesoscutum distinctly transversely striate; scutellum with longitudinal oblong striation; metanotum with faint transverse striation; propodeal enclosure transversely striate with shallow longitudinal depression medially, posterior surface of propodeum sometimes with small yellowish brown spot (
Fig. 4
); mesepisternum and propodeum side with fine striation, yellowish brown spot below tegula on upper mesopleuron (
Fig. 5
); metasoma black with fine setae (
Fig. 6
); petiole yellow or yellowish brown.
